http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Korean-school-to-train-farmers/article13991895.ece

Canaan Farmers School of South Korea has decided to train farmers from the backward areas of this district as part of the ‘New Village’ programme which was taken up in association with the Dr. B.R. Ambedkar University.The School will help farmers get more yield with the adoption of drought resistant seed technology in the areas where rainfall is scanty. Korean School president Kim-Bum-iL and Ambedkar varsity Vice-Chancellor H. Lajapathi Rai signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) to exchange ides in the field of education too on Saturday.